.TH SHAPEDUMP 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-shapetools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
shapedump \- print the coordinates of an ESRI shapefile
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shapedump
.I shapefile
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shapedump
reads the given ESRI shapefile and prints all path coordinates to
standard output. Each line contains four tab-separated columns: a
shape number, a vertex number within that shape, and the X and Y
coordinates. The shape number is incremented every time a new
sub-path begins.
.PP
The shape name is given without the
.I .shp
suffix; the companion
.IR .dbf ,
.IR .shx ,
.RI etc.\&
files in the same directory are read as needed.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I shapefile
The shapefile to dump, given without the trailing
.I .shp
suffix.
.SH EXAMPLES
Dump the coordinates of a Finland shapefile:
.PP
.RS 4
shapedump suomi > suomi.dat
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shape2xml (1),
.BR shapefind (1),
.BR shapefilter (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
Report issues at <https://github.com/fmidev/smartmet-shapetools/issues>.
